    • operateWithOperatorComponent

      private void operateWithOperatorComponent(String operator)
      Utility method. Operates with a component that is operator.

      This method implements a part of RPN algorithm. If operators' stack is empty, if its last element is a bracket, or if operator has higher priority than the last element in stack, operator is pushed into operators' stack.

      If an operator has equal or lower priority than last operator in operators' stack, this last operator in stack is pushed into output stack. Then this check is repeated until its conditions are not met. After that, operator is pushed into output stack.

      Parameters:
      operator - The operator.

    • operateWithBracketComponent

      private void operateWithBracketComponent(String bracket)
      Utility method. Operates with a component that is either open or close bracket.

      This method implements a part of RPN algorithm. If bracket is an open bracket, it is pushed into operators' stack. If bracket is a close bracket, operators are popped from operators' stack and pushed into output stack one by one until an open bracket becomes the top element of operators' stack. This open bracket is then deleted.

      Parameters:
      bracket - The bracket element.

    • comparePriorityWithLastInStack

      private int comparePriorityWithLastInStack(String operator)
      Utility method. Compares priority level of a passed operator with the last operator in operators' stack.
      Parameters:
      operator - The operator to check.
      Returns:
      1 if the priority of the passed operator is higher, or if operators' stack is empty, or if the top element of operators' stack is a bracket. -1 otherwise.
